  "fun_facts": [
    "Known as 'caustic potash' - the potassium equivalent of caustic soda (sodium hydroxide)",
    "Used in the Dutch process for cocoa - gives cocoa powder its darker color and milder, less acidic taste",
    "Makes SOFTER soap than sodium hydroxide - traditional 'soft soap' is made with potassium hydroxide",
    "Found in every alkaline battery (AA, AAA, etc.) as the electrolyte",
    "Used as a sodium-free alternative to sodium hydroxide in food processing for low-sodium products",
    "More expensive than sodium hydroxide, so it's used selectively when potassium is preferred over sodium"
  ]
